Animal Planet Heroes: Hurricane Reunions
description: Hurricanes Katrina and Rita left thousands of animals abandoned and alone, desperate to return to their owners. The documentary captures the harrowing rescues, heartwarming reunions, and the efforts of brave volunteers.

title: Les Khmers rouges, un procès contre l'oubli
Pipe Dreams
description: Remember your favorite bedtime story, or that kid that picked on you in third grade, or your first kiss, or going away to college, or that time your mom started smoking crack? She does. Come, laugh at her pain.

title: Canada Remembers: It's Time to Say Thanks
description: In August 2005, Thomega Entertainment in association with Credit Union Centre shot the second one hour documentary in their on going commitment to archive and broadcast these important Canadian legacy stories. This program featured Venessa Corkal and Phydra Faulkner, two teenage girls, who together discovered why it is important to never forget.

Food Network Special: Holidays at Walt Disney World Resort
MicroGravity

description: Learn to play Berry with Max Milligan.

Conversation Piece with Stephen Dwoskin
description: Shot in Brixton, London, in 2004, the film is originally a letter addressed to Dwoskin by its authors. It creates a unique space, movement and rhythm in which they develop his point of view on the evolution of cinema in the western world.

title: Faces of the Frontline
description: True American soldiers and heroes from World War II, Vietnam, the Persian Gulf War, Afghanistan, and Iraq tell their accounts of the natures of war and how it has changed their lives forever.

title: Tatsuo Ikeda's Wonder of the Spirit Box: I saw Ryoma Sakamoto!
description: First installment in Tatsuo Ikeda's "Wonder of the Spirit Box" series. Tatsuo Ikeda goes to Shikoku to contact Sakamoto Ryoma.

title: Pack Strap Swallow
description: This documentary follows the lives of American and European women who were drug mules and are now imprisoned in Ecuador.

title: Furiani, un siécle de passion
description: The story of the Stade de Furiani, a multi-purpose stadium in Furiani, Corsica, France, on the occasion of its 100th anniversary.

title: L'école des bérets verts
description: 15 soldiers from the French Marine appear at the start of Evaluation Course 123, aspiring to become marine commandos with the right to wear green berets. The French Special Forces consist of 2000 soldiers of which 450 belong to the Green Berets. The marine commandos are small units, which carry out extremely difficult missions behind the enemies' front line. Their tasks include sabotage, infiltration of enemies, release of hostages, capture of perpetrators of war crimes, evacuation of French citizens in need. The first group of French Green Berets was set up by Lieutenant Philippe Kieffer in Scotland during World War II. His methods of evaluation and selection of new commandos are still in use. For nine weeks the new aspirants undergo an extremely hard training, physically and mentally, day and night - in the air, on the ground and under water. The weakest are taken away quickly. Already after two weeks only 10 aspirants remain. After seven weeks of further hard training they receive their green berets at a ceremonial.

title: Guardian of Piri Remembered
description: Catherine Schell recounts her Space 1999 debut.

title: Adriana Calcanhoto - Adriana Partimpim Ao Vivo
Rights on the Line: Vigilantes at the Border
description: Exposes the ugly anti-immigrant politics that lurk behind the 'Minuteman Project' and similar vigilante groups. Shot by human rights activists and border residents, the video tells the story of border crossers and communities whose rights are being violated - and provides a close-up look at vigilantes through interviews and disturbing footage of their nighttime patrols.

title: Altri occhi
description: Federico lives near Rome, Matteo is from northern Italy. On first impression Federico is a sulky child, not very communicative. Matteo, on the other hand, is a restless child, who always seeks attention. They are both eight, and they have another element in common: they are blind. This film follows them in their daily lives, as they interact with their families, their friends, at school and on holiday. It's the story of two ordinary kids, their fears, their hopes, and their ordeals. Then, one day, the phone rings, and they meet: they are to take part in a film. It's the beginning of a new friendship.

title: O Último Comunista
description: Álvaro Cunhal (1913-2005) was at the head of the Portuguese Communist Party for more than half a century. Born in a bourgeois family, he maintains himself very close to the soviet leaders, from Stalin to Brejnev. In exile or in prison most of the time in his youth, he played a major role during the Portuguese revolution (1974/75). A talented writer and artist, he defended the hard communist line until his death. Rare archive footage reveals this enigmatic figure.

title: Peckerwood, WV: A Portrait of Artist Mary Potter
description: Mary Potter is an environmental artist and furnituremaker who lives outside Franklin, West Virginia in a place she calls Peckerwood. Her materials come from nature, junk heaps and friend's garages. Her collaborators/conspirators are the blacksmiths, carpenters and hired hands in her small rural community.

title: Ramping It Up: The Making of Dishdogz
Lame d'un père, l'âme d'un sabre
description: A documentary about the making of the "Lone Wolf and Cub" film series with interviews from many of the crew members from the films.

title: Force of the Spirit
description: Force of the Spirit is a documentary about courage and triumph in the face of adversity. Jean Jacques Machado, born without a functioning left hand, overcomes all challenges to become one of the world's greatest hand-to-hand combat grapplers. This is the legendary story of a world champion. Awe-inspiring and inspirational, Machado demonstrates that it's not what's on the outside that determines a person, but rather what's on the inside. His story confirms that dreams can come true when you're willing to confront the challenges life deals you. With never before seen footage, witness evolution's most advanced warrior, his extraordinary fighting art and his influence on the lives of others who found encouragement by his example.

title: Nou, dat was het dan!
description: In 1980 film writer Ruud den Drijver goes head to head with two notorious Dutch film directors, Paul Verhoeven and Wim Verstappen, passionate film makers, competitors and colleagues in a free for all heated discussion ranging (among other subjects) from oral sex to the art of motion pictures. 25 years later the confrontation is continued during the Cannes Film Festival. In the meantime Wim Verstappen has died a year earlier and Paul Verhoeven has returned from a brilliant career in the States. Paul is still very outspoken. He talks freely about the present-day neo-conservative policies of America, and about the situation in Hollywood and his work. THAT'S IT !!! (English title) (1980-2005) is a retrospective view on the careers of two driven film directors and is a hilarious time document larded with passionate statements.

title: Amagakeru seishun: Nippon o aishita yuushitachi
Broken: How to Make DV Look Like Film

title: Pagolin Soccer Project
description: A short documentary about children in a Tanzanian soccer program who do not have the proper gear for the only activity that brings them hope.

title: A Walk Across Venice

title: Save Your Legs
description: 'Save Your Legs!' is the mystical story of a bold sporting adventure. How does a team of cowboy Aussie cricketers take on a billion cricket-mad Indians on their own turf? This engaging tale shows how the childhood dreams of the humble Abbotsford Anglers Cricket Club meet the harsh realities of the Sub Continent.

title: Luther - Sein Leben, Weg und Erbe
description: Only few historical figures have affected modern society and humanity as enduringly as Martin Luther, and on such a global scale. This comprehensive and methodically produced documentary traces the footsteps of the Great Reformer and reflects upon the places and districts which have become inseparably connected with his name. Furthermore, besides including scenes from the successful cinema feature film "LUTHER" numerous experts also discuss the life and work of Martin Luther.

title: Anne Murray: The Music of My Life
The Gates: Deep Saffron
description: Christo and Jeanne-Claude created a masterpiece known simply as 'The Gates' of Central Park in New York City. Follow the temporary life and 'The Gates' through inception, installation, enjoyment and disassembly.

title: Point of No Return
description: How does it feel to be stolen from the place you call home - never to return? Point of No Return takes viewers on a spirtual journey to the slave dungeons in Elmina and Cape Coast, Ghana, the place where millions of Africans breathed their last breath in their motherland Africa. Watch to bear witness to the remains of this tragedy of humankind, and to ponder its impact on present-day Ghana and America.

title: 20 Jahre 'Lindenstraße' - Die Geburtstagsshow
description: 20 years 'Lindenstraße' - The birthday show.

title: Covjek kojeg nema
description: Documentary on the only Croatian Nobel Prize winner - Ivo Andric.

title: Vive l'indépendance du Texas!
description: When I was a kid, my father recounted the Algerian War. These were fanciful events, which he had experienced when he was 20 years old. For 35 years, I have had them in mind. At first, I thought it was beyond epic. I find it less funny now.

title: Jakten på 'Elektron'
description: When Norwegian officers boarded a Russian trawler, the last thing they expected was to be abducted. But for 5 days, they were held prisoner while the navy chased the ship. "We closed all the hatches and prepared for war", states Valery Jarantsev, captain of the Russian trawler, Elektron. When two Norwegian officials caught his ship illegally fishing, he defied their orders to return to port. Instead, he abducted the Norwegian officials and made a mad dash for Russia. "He was quite determined. He didn't show any signs of surrendering", recalls abducted officer Henning Thune. Another Russian trawler came to Elektron's aid, preventing it being intercepted by the coast guard and the ship entered Russian waters. But Jarantsev is now being prosecuted by his own government, after they reached a deal with Norway. He faces up to seven years in prison. TV2

The Desert Vipers Motorcycle Club presents the Adelanto Grand Prix! Side Hacks, Vintage Bikes, Quads, Team Race and a carnival of friends, family, and fun of two full days of hard charging racing action!

title: Play Beck with Max Milligan
description: Play Beck With Max Milligan.

title: Iran Land of Religions (Sunni Minority)
description: When human beings studied magnificent manifestations of creation in nature, they concluded that the creator of all those wonders and all that magnificence and beauty should be bigger and more powerful than all the gods whose statues were made by humans. Now, the thoughtful Man was thinking about God; the merciful God who stood above all and ruled the destiny of the universe. Iran has always been a land of religions through millennia. It is the burying place of 13 prophets as well as renowned religious personalities of Christians, Jews, Zoroastrians, and other religious minorities. The country has also been the birthplace of Zoroastrianism. Iran abounds with all kinds of religious places: some of the earliest churches built in the world as well as thousands of exquisitely built mosques. The coexistence of millions of followers of the said faiths in Iran has turned the country into a land of the plurality of religions which is full of cultural diversity and attractions. Followers of all religious faiths have been living peacefully in the country for centuries.

title: Solitudes
description: In many cities, the number of lodgings with people on their own has exceeded family households. Something never seen before. Solitudes brings you inside the house of 64 people of all ages and from all different backgrounds. Touching confidences over life as a single and an omnipresent television connect all these individuals together.

title: Journey to the Heart of the Tsunami: Unstoppable Wave
description: An major expedition organised by Darlow Smithson involving the world's top scientists to explore the site of the Banda Aceh Earthquake, three miles below the Indian Ocean which caused the devastating Tsunami of 2004.

title: Befrielsens mindretal - Det danske mindretal
description: Documentary about the Danish minority in Germany after WWII.

title: Women in Canada: A Trilogy
description: A history of women in Canada, told as a trilogy. These true stories are more twisted dream than dreary history lesson.

title: Dionisio Ridruejo, la forja de un demócrata

description: Second installment in Tatsuo Ikeda's "Wonder of the Spirit Box" series. This time Tatsuo Ikeda goes to Kagoshima to contact Takamori Saigo.

description: A documentary about the importance of writing. It follows different people with their own variations when it comes to writing, from people who follow scientific ideals of the language and others who use it to best accommodate with the way they use language to communicate.

title: Abendläuten - Eine Reise mit Rudolf Wessely
Oscar Night
description: Instead of their usual Book Club Meeting the ladies dress up and walk the red carpet into "Oscar Night". A night dedicated to celebrate the Oscar's - Book Club style. The Book Club meeting is turned into an all girl's party complete with gowns, red carpet, champagne, and movie presentations.

Mi huelva tiene una ría
description: A young woman, filmmaker Mavi Villatoro Ruiz, tells the story of her family's native Huelva - a southwestern Andalusian Spanish town on the banks of the Odiel and Tinto rivers - struggling to save its waterways and environment from toxic waste and pollution.

title: Quo vadis?
description: Samir Abdallah films the quest for identity and roots of his two sons. A trip which takes them from the parisian suburbs to their countries of origin : Denmark, Morocco, Egypt...

title: Enfants de Noma
description: A sensible approach of this misrecognized disease called Noma. This often deadly disease affects about 100,000 children a year in Africa, South America and South Asia. Shot in Niger, this documentary follows some of these children during their treatment, in a hospital of the ONG "Sentinelles" which struggles against Noma's development, with local teams. The children affected by Noma are rejected by the population, even their own parents. Alone with their pain, they show great courage and determination to get better: you never see them cry, they actually smile.

title: About FAQ
description: Four crew and cast members talk about the movie "FAQ: Frequently Asked Questions".

title: Hennabandan e Dictator
description: Interview with a Kurdish woman who puts Saddam Hussein on her personal trial.

title: False Dawn: The Promise of Apollo
description: 1960's America was deeply divided. The civil rights movement and severe poverty upset the established order. The Cuban Missile Crisis brought us to the brink of nuclear war, and the fear of Communism across the world swept through Middle America like wild fire, giving rise to the U.S. intervention in Vietnam. Then President Kennedy launched the inspirational race to the moon--a quest for mankind to conquer technological difficulties and explore space. The massive cost - at a time when millions of Americans lived below the poverty line - was justified to take the first step to meaningful exploration of space, understanding our universe and breaking free from our small but beautiful planet to live among the stars. The Apollo moon landings promised much, but ultimately amounted to a "false dawn." Recently released transcripts of White House meetings support the theory that the president only supported moon missions to detract attention from the escalating domestic and international situation and prove that Communism was inferior. In the first decade of the New Millennium, we have witnessed the tragedy of 9/11, the war on terrorism, multi-national forces in Iraq and Afghanistan in a deeply unpopular "occupation" and mounting tensions over Iran. And yet, in the midst of these developments, the U.S. Space Program has again been put at the forefront of the political agenda by President George W. Bush's "New Vision for Space"--advocating a return to the moon and beyond by 2010. But is this another "false dawn?" The debate starts here.

title: Last of the Spanish Mustangs
description: A man connects with a rare herd of Arizona mustangs and exposes a government agency and lying politicians who break laws to ship their meat abroad for human consumption.

title: Leap of Faith
description: The story of a miracle healing and how it changed the family, 30 years later.

title: Q & A with Jana Sevcikova and Werner Herzog
Henri Tomasi, un idéal universel
description: A look back at the career of one of the least known and most brilliant composers and conductors of his generation: Henri Tomasi.

title: The Dwarves: Fuck You Up and Get Live
The Oriental Dreams
description: The palace of "Chehel Sotoun" is one of the most elegant edifices of all Persian monuments. This masterpiece influences the spread of the fame of the Persian civilization to Europe. The "Chehel Sotoun" palace was built in the seventeenth century to lodge foreign guests, such as kings, princes, and ambassadors of important countries. That is why this edifice was built elegant.

title: Rimini. Un itinerario tra storia, monumenti e opere d'arte

description: This documentary short shows how composer Danny Elfman created each of the Oompa-Loompa songs for Tim Burton's 'Charlie and the Chocolate Factory' (2005).

Beyond the Moon: Failure Is Not an Option 2
description: A history of the U.S. manned space program from the end of Apollo to today, as seen by the men (and women) of Mission Control.

title: La santa muerte, superstición o fe
description: The cult of the Holy Death and its ever more notorious manifestations have been the cause of scandal for some and the object of study for others. This strange social phenomenon does not only have its basis in the history of Mexican traditions, but rather, as this analysis shows, it helps us to explain and come to know better present-day Mexican society.

title: In the Grip of the Great Depression
description: In the grip of the Great Depression we take a look at the challenges that the people of Britton, South Dakota had to face during the 30's. This historic film captures the resolute spirit and never-say-die attitude.

title: Manaus, un opéra dans la jungle brésilienne
Estamos ganando, periodismo y censura en la guerra de Malvinas
Lopukhovo
description: Lopukhovo... a forgotten Ukrainian village deep in the heart of the Carpthian forest, suspended between the dismantling of the ex-Sovietic Union and the approach of the new European Union.

title: The Forgotten Refugees
description: Mizrahi Jews remember their lives in Arab countries, their expulsion, and their coming to Israel.

title: On the Roof of Asia
description: On the roof of Asia, I saw birds who like me, were strangers in this land coming from far away. I'm a stranger too, a foreigner, feeling lost in the blue dream of the journey to Isfahan. The "Naghshe-Jehan" Square which is the center and the heart of Isfahan, is the main subject of my sketches. The date of its construction goes back to 1600 AD after which the Imam Mosque, the "Sheikh Lotfollah Mosques, the "Gheisariyeh" Bazaar, and the "Ali-Ghaapu" Palace were erected. During the reign of Shah Abbas the Great, the square hosted polo games. At present, it is a place of business and trade, of group-games and recreation in the afternoons. it is a gathering place for people from all walks of life.

title: Conan Doyle for the Defence
description: Documentary exploring the lesser-known side of Arthur Conan Doyle, who solved real crimes as chilling and baffling as those investigated by his creation Sherlock Holmes.

title: Peace Looks Like This
description: Using their own self-created artwork to explore a deep and important subject, school kids explain their understandings of the word 'Peace'. Inter cut with many of their vibrant and richly expressive drawings, the kids' verbal responses are by turns poignant, funny, spooky and insightful. It offers a glimpse into what kids are learning about our society and culture and what they are likely to carry on into their lives as adults.

title: A Corner of Her Eye
description: Three brothers ride out Hurricane Katrina in their father's house in Bay St. Louis, Mississippi. An intimate, spooky family portrait that starts as a father's adventurous challenge and rapidly turns to a fight for survival.

title: Stiller Schrei - Leben nach dem Albtraum
Tatsuo Ikeda's Scary Story That Can't be Broadcast: Signpost to the Dark Road Gaki
description: Third installment in Tatsuo Ikeda's "Scary Story That Can't be Broadcast" series.

Petit à petit
description: Déborah, Marc, Dylan, Bastien, Camille and the others are between two and three years old and are starting school. These children are living the adventure of their first year of kindergarten. Without commentary, at the pace of a local school, we discover with them their new world almost day by day, and how, little by little, they are building themselves.

title: I Am Woman
description: Is there something universal that connects black women across the globe? 10 black female performers from South Africa and the USA decide to find out. This raw, honest and emotional film ultimately interrogates what it means to be an African and a black woman.

title: Te chlopaki
description: Short documentary about The Analogs - Polish punk band created in 1995 in Szczecin. Movie was added as a bonus material on "Najlepsze z najgorszych" album.

title: One Day Sale
description: Come along to the local Best Buy where shoppers are waiting for the clock to strike 6:00am so they can rush into the store to 'go and grab' their bargains. One Day Sale gives a brief glimpse of an interesting group of people that only act this way once a year.

title: President George H.W. Bush: Speeches of the 41st President of the United States 1989-1993
description: The 41st President's greatest speeches from 1989-1993, including the national address on Iraq's invasion of Kuwait, his address to the nation on Panama's police action, and his speech at the end of the Gulf War.

title: Vibrations
description: Improvised "document", attempting to capture the vibrations that precede and follow live music. Sharp and deceptive, playing with the architecture of the Kid Ailack Art Hall, they run along walls, making the air tremble and strings, membranes and eardrums shiver.

title: Out of the Cage
description: Getting an up-close and person look into the lives of the homeless, through candid conversations on politics, drugs and current affairs.

title: Atla
description: Two Bedouins, a white woman and two heavily packed camels traveling by feet through the Sinai desert, A rough and impressively desolate area. They are entering a world of emptiness and silence.

title: Keep Em' Rollin'
description: Documentary on the production of films in the silent era.

title: Tell It with Puppets
description: Most children are able to use a flat felt hand puppet and a simple rod puppet to express and create stories they know and invent. This film gives a simple 5-Step recipe for adults and children to follow in putting together a puppet show.

title: Fish & Stone
description: Whenever I remember the water-stone in the middle of the vestibule in the Chahar Baagh school, my heart lights up. Water-stones have the name of God in their breasts and are set up at sacred places to satiate the thirst of the thirsty. It's such a pity to find them so empty of water. And so, the water-stone which had been devoid of water and fish for hundreds of years was filled to the brim with fish and water in my frenzied mind.

title: Just People (in Love)
description: When Chris returns to life with the Just People group, Lana and Michelle's friendship is put to the test. Who will be his new girlfriend? How long will he stay? How will the staffers manage this potentially problematic romance?

description: A new documentary created from camcorder and cinecamera footage, commissioned by The Hayward Gallery, London.

title: Dear Father, Quiet, We're Shooting...
description: When war crimes are carried out under orders from officers, military commanders, and political leaders, who is responsible? This film allows former members of the Israeli Defense Forces - now conscientious objectors-to recount their experiences in both Lebanon and Palestine, and to question the limits of state power.

title: Memories of Norfolk & Western 611
description: Footage of the renowned Norfolk and Western J-class 4-8-4 steam locomotive number 611 operating in southern Ohio and northern Kentucky, taken from 1992 to 1994, before it was retired from service.

title: Anarchy Ahead: The Harvesting of American Families
description: Ground Breaking Documentary about the real cost of raising an emotionally well balanced child in today's high conflict divorce society.

title: Jiyuu Ajia no eikou: Tatakau Biruma dokuritsu giyuugun Indo kokumingun
One on One
description: The new adventure sport of mountain unicycling is shown in the mountains above Santa Barbara. This unusual sport has its attractions and its difficulties, its beauty and its beast.

title: Taxi Blues
description: In the metropolis of Seoul over 70.000 taxi's take part in the traffic. On an average day, a taxi driver has 20 to 30 trips and works 12 hour shifts. They go to every part of the city and transport a variety of passengers. Taxi Blues is the story of a man who one day also became one of those 70.000 taxi drivers.

title: Directing Lloyd
description: Justin Remer discusses the experience of casting Lloyd Kaufman and working with him on the film IN DEFENSE OF LEMMINGS. This is a bonus feature on the BEST OF TROMADANCE FILM FESTIVAL, VOL. 4 DVD.

title: Seven Oaks: The Seeds of Western Canada
If I Were a Saxophone
description: A modern-day Cinderella story, focusing on a 23-year old musician for whom the saxophone has proved to be both an inspiration and a practical means of escape from a life of dreariness in a Ukrainian orphanage. Now Veronica has been accepted to pursue higher studies at elite institutions in Eastern Europe, a development which offers her both a clear and direct way to the top of the performing arts world and yet another round of displacement. The camera follows her as a main character and a visual subject: a striking red-haired girl, through crowded streams of unknown faces, car traffic, and the waves of the sea. Between the storms of ovation and the loneliness of nights, she struggles to fulfill the dream of a lifetime.

title: La toma de la Plaza
description: A blood offering to Mother Earth takes place every year in the region of Cotacachi Volcano in Ecuador. Once a year, for centuries, the two main indigenous communities have fought against each other at the main square of the city of Cotacachi. The aim is to conquer the square and to demonstrate the power of the indigenous people in a mestizo world.

title: Mehdi Zana, voir la vie autrement
Dokuritsu Ajia no hikaru: Daitoua sensou to Indoneshia Marêshia no dokuritsu
Biped & Pond Way: A Film
description: Reunites two films, Biped (49 min.) and Pond Way (26 min.) both by Charles Atlas, shot during the Merce Cunningham Dance Company shows of the same names. Recorded in 1999 in Mulhouse, France.

title: The Soller Railway
description: Follows the famous Soller train from Palma to Soller, with information about the train itself, the history of the line, and the journey.

title: Another African Story
description: Documentary on the humanitarian crisis and the conflict in Darfur, Sudan.

title: Lapskaus Boulevard
description: The fresh produce store Nordic Deli in Brooklyn, NY, has been run by the Bakke family since 1958. In the third generation, they produces and sell traditional Norwegian food over the counter in the street called Lapskaus Boulevard.

title: The Adventures of Benjamin Schmid
description: Documentary by Tony Palmer about the famous classical violinist Benjamin Schmid. Featuring footage from the opening concert of the Salzburg Festival from 1986

title: From the Ashes: The Untold Story of Ground Zero
Bon Jovi: The Broadcast Archives
description: New Jersey Rock band Bon Jovi play live at various events and shows during the 1980's and 1990's. Includes performances from The first Farm Aid concert and The David Letterman Show.

title: Im Auftrag seiner Majestät - Ein barocker Bücherkrimi
description: For centuries, libraries have been a repository of knowledge and power.

title: Imagine 02: A Celebration of Children's Hospital Los Angeles
Falling Through
description: This documentary revisits the classroom shooting that occurred at Monash University, Australia in 2002 in which two students were killed and several others injured. Through the use of interviews with students and teachers, evidence from the trial and archival news footage the story is pieced together to reveal the portrait of a young man and his decline into a mental breakdown.

title: Hey Rain
description: Hey Rain is a documentary that looks at the life of folklorist Bill Scott who traveled throughout Australia collecting folk material, writing stories, songs, and poems editing over thirty books on the stories and songs of Australia. It talks to some of the many folk musicians who were inspired by him.

title: Niagara Falls
description: A charming young woman discusses the wonders of her hometown of Niagara Falls, New York. Through her descriptions and stories we move beyond the cliche of Niagara Falls as a tacky tourist destination and begin to see the richness of that magnificent place that some people are lucky enough to call home.

title: Au coeur du rêve
description: Internationally recognized, the Western Australian Aboriginal Gija painters impose their signs and connect, in one draught, the world of Western contemporary art and an ancestral ritual practice whose roots are several thousand years old.

title: Baja: The Other California
description: Baja California stretches 750 miles southwards from its famous neighbour, the State of California. On either side of this narrow strip of land lie the rich waters of the Pacific and the Sea of Cortez.

title: Københavns nyere befæstning - Søbefæstningen
description: The story of Copenhagen's coastal defense structure, built 150 years ago. The third part of a trilogy on Copenhagen's defense structures in recent times.

title: First Steps: International Response to the Landmine Crisis
Street Racing: A Night on Earth
Crafting Your Career: How to Turn Your Hobby Into a Business
description: Priscilla Hauser, the decorative painter, tells the story of how she turned her hobby into a career and offers advice to viewers who would like to do the same.

title: Fatal Attraction
description: A look at frivolous one night stand which can have deadly consequences.

title: Folding Paper Cranes: The Poetry of an Atomic Veteran, Leonard 'Red' Bird
description: A nation goes to war without ever firing a shot against its enemy. Instead, it turns the most devastating weapon known to man against its own population.Casualties: approximately 80,000 wounded and 17,000 killed. Leonard 'Red' Bird was one of these casualties. This is his story.

title: Ovas de Oro
description: An eye-opening documentary about the salmon industry in Chile and its impact on communities, workers and the environment.

title: Where Words Prevail
description: Where Words Prevail explores the widely acclaimed work of Cicely Berry, Voice Director of the Royal Shakespeare Company (RSC). Berry's voice techniques are invaluable to the actors and directors who are performing both classical and modern plays in today's theaters. From rehearsals at the RSC in Stratford-upon-Avon, to workshops in Moscow, New York, Seoul, and the Favellas of Rio de Janeiro, Berry's work is documented in diverse languages, producing new understanding of the power of voice, language, and communications.

title: End Time Revelation: John's Apocalyptic Message to the Seven Churches
description: From his seclusion on the Greek island of Patmos, John wrote letters to the 7 Churches that revealed his vision of the future and the pathway he saw for achieving peace of mind in an uncertain world. The coming of the 4 Horseman of the Apocalypse and the earth's last great crisis are all part of John's vision. Could these messages have meaning for mankind today?

title: Plan-séquence d'une mort criée
description: In the Gypsy quarter of a village in Transylvania, an old woman has died. During the two nights preceding the funeral, family, friends and neighbors follow one another at his bedside to accompany his departure in music. Their lamentations are captured crescendo by the camera in a single take.

title: Gente como Nós - Vidas de Imigrantes em Portugal
Life and Times of Wayne Gretzky
Mordfall John Lennon - Das Idol und sein Attentäter
description: 25 years ago on the 8th December 1980 John Lennon was shot by Mark David Chapman. This documentary shows the parallels between the murderer and his idol, asks the question, why a former fan (Chapman) began to hate his idol and finally killed him. In archive footage of interviews on audio tapes Chapman talks about his motives. Psychologists and confidants of Chapman debate on possible reasons of his act. Frederic Seaman, a friend of John Lennon, gives insights of Lennons life behind the curtains.

title: Honto Ni Atta! Noroi No Video 18
description: 18th entry in the popular "Honto ni Atta. Noroi no Video" series.

title: Bounce Like a Ball: Life at 105
description: This is the tale of a remarkably lively and strong-willed woman, Ruth Hickox. At 105 years old she takes care of herself while still living in the house her father built. Her only wish is to die in the house she has lived in for over 100 years.

title: Scratching the Surface: Japan
description: A documentary about the underground hip-hop culture in Japan as of 2003. It capture a thriving underground hip-hop scene, touching on a diverse range of artists including graffiti writers, rappers, beat-boxers, breakers.

title: A Comic's Climb at the USCAF
description: American-born comedian Des Bishop is a star in Ireland but tries to get discovered in his birth country at the US Comedy Arts Festival.

title: North American Grilled Cheese
description: A brief introduction to life cycle of the North American Grilled Cheese.

title: Don Quijote vive aquí
description: "Don Quixote" never existed, it's a character written by Cervantes - isn't it?

title: La classe de madame Lise
description: A culturally diverse first-grade class who live in the most multi-ethnic district of Montreal overcome their numerous differences, inspiring genuine confidence in the future generation.

title: Sluts: The Documentary
description: 8 women between the ages of 17 to 82 discuss what is was like to be labeled as a slut.

title: Fine Living Network and CNET Present: The Home Entertainment Upgrade
description: Fine Living and CNET bring you the Ultimate Home Entertainment Upgrade. The special has the look and feel of Home Entertainment itself: shooting High Def in a 16:9 aspect ratio, with a visual and editorial style and graphics that reflect the worlds of cinema, DVD, games and online. Focusing on lifestyle and room design as much as the technology that lives within it, this special is chock full of useful takeaway information. Two very different households are taken through the process of a home entertainment upgrade at two different budget levels. At a budget of $25,000 the couple in their hip loft space employ experts to design and install their state of the art plasma screen HDTV with surround sound. At a budget of $5,000 the couple in their pre-fab modern home do it themselves, with a little help from host and CNET.com expert Brian Cooley. Each end up with a satisfying HDTV/surround sound system that can really rock the house.

title: Deru Kugi Wa Utareru
description: The number two producer of music in the world is hardly a major player when it comes worldwide recognition. After this film, all of that will change. The Land of the Rising Sun: Japan will be dominating your ears like their cars that have taken over the world!

title: The Colour of Memory: Conversations with Guido Molinari
description: A portrait of major Canadian artist Guido Molinari, during the last year of his life.

title: The Demining Camp
description: Some fought on opposite sides in the war which ravaged Mozambique. Others were civilians, and for them, the demining work is an alternative to unemployment or a life of crime. Living all together in tents, they stay for long periods far from their families. Every day they risk their lives together. They are indeed a very special group of men.

title: Cereal Wormholes They Are All Real
description: For thousands of years, an alien presence here on Earth has made us aware of their existence through miraculous signs and wonders, such as the Nazca Lines of Peru, the Pyramids of Egypt, Stonehenge in England, and now, the global phenomena of Crop Circles. Presented here for the first time are the details of an investigation into the extra-dimensional aspects of the Crop Circle phenomena.

title: Boneyard: Where Machines End Their Lives
description: The story of how ships, airplanes, missiles, steel from the World Trade Center, and nuclear weapons cores, having reached the end of their useful lives, are sent to "boneyards" to be stored, reused, sold, disassembled for parts, or scrapped and recycled.

title: Ayurveda: Moeder van alle geneeswijzen
description: Ayurveda the Mother of all medicines. Never has Ayurveda been filmed before in this astonishing way. In this documentary you are invited into the life and work from the South Indian Ayurveda physician Dr. V.P. Mohana Kumari. The introduction explains the background and philosophy of Ayurveda. Astasthana Pareeksha shows you the procedure of an Ayurveda consult. Preventive and healing is the well known Pancha Karma course. This treatment is shown in close detail through the eyes of a client. Last the unique approach to treat mental diseases through an ancient spiritual color therapy, 'Kalam Ezhutu'.

title: À l'ombre des grands chênes (Abel Gance)
Phandom
description: Interviews with several crew members who entered the film business because of interest (of varying degrees) in the Phantasm film series.

title: Play Frusciante with Max Milligan
description: Learn to play frusciante with Max Milligan.

title: Play Les Paul with Max Milligan
description: Learn to play Les Paul with Max Milligan.

title: Jag tänker på mig själv - och vänstern
Ana Terra
description: The composer Ana Terra talks about her work and life in its most intimate and personal aspects as well as the world of ideas and politics.

title: Charlie and the Chocolate Factory: Under the Wrapper
description: This documentary short explores the fascinating array of special and visual effects used to bring Wonka's factory to life on screen in Tim Burton's 'Charlie and the Chocolate Factory' (2005).

title: Big Fish/Small Fry: Urban Angling in New York
description: Following two fishermen from different parts of New York City, this film explores what the sport means to anglers young and old. While adults like Anthony relax in Brooklyn???s Prospect Park, 12-year old Polito and his friends compete for bass in the waters of East Harlem. A portrait emerges of an urban subculture that revolves around camaraderie and a search for the natural world within the city.

title: Le 17, Hôtel de police
description: The everyday life of a police station, located in Créteil, in the Val-de-Marne department, France.

title: On Every Corner
description: An in depth look at the art of Street Performing (busking) in the City of Pittsburgh.

title: Me and Graham: The Soundtrack of Our Lives
description: A documentary about two baby-boomer British ex-pats, who make a journey to the UK, New York and Los Angeles in search of and in celebration of the Beatles FAN!

title: Quail's Quest: It's a Boy! - The Premiere
description: The premiere event for the film Quail's First Christmas (2005) including interviews with cast and crew.

title: Befrielsens mindretal - Det tyske mindretal
description: Documentary about the German minority in Denmark after WWII.

title: Sukumizu a GO! GO! GO! side: A
School Mizugi Audition PART 8 Love Love Mizugi-hen
Dubbed
description: Girls. Money. Neon. One could say the import car scene has gone the way of Hollywood: cram as much eye-candy in as possible, plaster a scantily-clad girl on the cover and hope for the "bling." Ditching hype in exchange for integrity, dubbed redefines the automotive documentary by exploring the honest world of euro-car tuning. Working together to maintain and improve, the VW enthusiast culture revels in turning once "grocery-getter" sports coupes into exotic-killers. Dubbed compliments reverent and unapologetic interviews with unadulterated cinematography composed by VW enthusiasts and student filmmakers. Following the experiences of a grass-roots race car driver, a die-hard enthusiast couple and a former show-winning tour guide, dubbed covers the joys, laughs, struggles, and heart-felt losses sustained by this disenchanting yet steadfastly supported sub-culture.

title: A Very British Bollywood
description: Documentary about the Bollywood film industry.

title: The Passion of the Cup
description: Canadian National Barista Champion Sammy Piccolo wants to make your daily coffee an uncommon pleasure. In Sammy's mind, if you do it everyday, why not make something that tastes delicious?

title: Ballroom Babies
description: One hour observational documentary produced by iKandy Films for ABC TV about the highly competitive world of junior ballroom dancing. Every year the best junior ballroom dancers in the country compete in the Australian Dancesport Championships. Only the tough will survive. Some children will lose, others triumph.

title: Klimatické zariadenie má poruchu
description: A Slovak documentary that illustrates how civilization and agriculture are contributing to current climate change and greenhouse gas emissions. It explains why it is unsustainable to replace greenery with concrete meadows, emphasizing the significance of vegetation for the climate. Additionally, it discusses issues related to an irresponsible economy.

title: Rom & Cola
description: Two twin brothers opens together a bar in Rome.

title: Folter in Stammheim? - Die Propaganda der RAF
description: "Torture in Stammheim prison." When a law enforcement officer unravels the cells on the seventh floor of the prison tower, he makes a discovery that will affect politics and the judiciary, the press and the public for decades.

title: Diarios de Bagdad
description: Iraq is a country that suffers from the devastating consequences of the overthrow of a dictatorial regime, gradually weakened by international commercial sanctions and finally put down by the armed intervention headed by the United States army. The enormous destruction of the country combined with the sabotages and attacks perpetrated by the terrorist guerrillas paint a desperate panorama for the civilian population that cannot find any recourse other than to continue fighting for its beliefs and survival.

title: Sabine Weiss, un regard sur le temps
Franco Nero in His Own Words
Harold Lloyd Comedy Collection: Mini Biographies
Hollywood Sem Filtro 2
description: How advertising influences the lives of all of us on a daily basis.

title: The Last Chance
description: A prison in Galilee is the setting for this film about a withdrawal and rehabilitation department for heavy drug addicts. The Last Chance is a powerful film that documents an all-too common social problem. It is also the compelling story of one man who will lose everything if he cannot find the strength to beat his addiction once and for all.

title: Le monde en croisières
description: Travel the world and its amazing oceans and seas aboard the most beautiful cruise ships of our time.

title: The Ballad of Vicki and Jake
description: is the story of Vicki, a single mother struggling with addiction, and her young son, Jake. The film opens as Vicki and Jake are beginning a new chapter in their lives, moving from a homeless shelter into their own council house. But however hard Vicki tries create a home for herself and her son, she is unable to ignore old problems and avoid new ones that arise. Shot with hard-headed honesty, Vicki and Jake combines uncompromising interviews, scenes of drug abuse and touching intimacy between mother and son. It is a film of extremes, and as Vicki finds herself losing control the story shifts to the relationship between Vicki and the filmmakers, neither of whom will give up their quest for a happy ending without a fight.

title: From a Silk Cocoon
description: Labeled as "disloyal" and deemed "enemy aliens dangerous to the public peace and safety of the United States," a young Japanese American couple, held in separate American prison camps during WW II, struggle to prove their innocence and fight deportation. With the discovery of their actual letters, diaries, and haiku poetry, the story reveals the frightening and tragic outcome resulting from wartime hysteria and racial profiling. A story of love and survival, Shizuko and Itaru, renounce their American citizenship in protest and then must face the reality of raising their children in war-torn Japan.

title: Fremde Liebe
description: A teenage Tuareg girl Rhaissa is about to marry a man she has never met. She learns from her girlfriend that her husband-to-be is not very handsome nor has an abundance of "ashek" or pride.

title: Analyzing 'Dark Water'
description: This short making-of consists of 3 parts: Blue Robe (2:49), Wall of Water (2:46) and Interactive Bathroom Sequence (1:38).

title: The 80s: Downtown
description: A look at the culture of 1980s New York.

title: Don't Forget the Joie de Vivre
Chimps: A Whisper Away from Us
originalTitle: Chimps: A Whisper Away From Us

title: Quest for the Real Paul
description: Go on a fascinating journey to many of the places where the apostle traveled and taught. Along the way, scholar David Hulme begins to unravel the centuries of accumulated misunderstanding about Paul and his teachings. With modern scholarship shedding new light on the biblical record, an astonishingly different picture of the apostle Paul emerges.

title: Gente do Salto
description: A collection of seven documentary films on the memories of Portuguese people who fled to France in the 1960s, including a feature film, La photo déchirée, chronique d'une émigration clandestine (2002), and six previously unreleased short films produced by the same director, José Vieira.

title: Rees Howells, Intercessor
description: Documentary on the Bible College of Wales, from its beginnings through to the present day, focusing on founder Rees Howells. Dramatised re-enactments and narration combine with interviews of former staff and students.

title: Musoya, malgré le silence
description: Discover four women from Mali, committed, festive women, mothers and wives, from whom we have a lot to learn.

title: Histoire d'être humain
description: A look at public education at a Montreal high school.

title: Glamour of War
description: Alison Reiss, a performance artist and model, curators a show devoted to the anniversary of 9/11. This documentary by Chas Krstich brings us into the event, a show a happening and shows us who this charismatic woman is.

title: The Art of Eric Gill
description: The Art of Eric Gill presents many of Gill's most important works, and has a soundtrack drawn entirely from Gill's compendious and controversial writings.

title: Behind the Scenes of Everything You Want?
Play Santana with Max Milligan
description: Learn to play Santana with Max Milligan.

title: Play Allman with Max Milligan
description: Learn to play Allman with Max Milligan.

title: Neon Venus Rockumentary on MTV Espanol
description: The Alterlatino band Neon Venus tours for the Armed Forces stationed in Egypt, the Sinai, Italy, Spain and Turkey.

title: How I Went at TromaFling and Introduced My Films
Avant les assises, l'intention de tuer
Judy and Donatello
description: Judy meets Donatello in Florence during the 60s. I am their daughter trying to picture the atmosphere of those days with interviews with their friends and a reconstruction of the meeting.

title: Keeping It Real
description: 'Keeping it real' tells the story of Manchester's Anthony Wilson and his new hip hop act Raw T. A decade since the closure of the Hacienda and the demise of Factory Records, this documenray explores why Anthony is motivated to bid once more for success,in a city re-born through music.

title: Last Flight to Berlin
description: In this film Robert Linnell (a filmmaker) documents in a personal way his father's war story on film. Robert Linnell never knew his father. His father was the pilot of a heavy bomber and was was shot down on a night bombing mission to Berlin in Germany in 1944. Linnell was only 2 months old when his father died. In this short film Linnell includes historical footage, accesses historical documents, interviews with family and other pilots who survived, a visit the forest in Germany near Berlin where his father's plane crashed after being shot down by a German night-fighter. Incredibly, Linnell managed to track down the pilot of the German night fighter who shot down his father's plane. A moving and personal account.

title: WWIII Blues
description: An essay film investigating popular culture, nuclear war and family insanity.

title: Pas de pays, sans paysans
description: Farmer and director Ève Lamont talks to farmers about their solutions to challenge the hegemony of factory farms in the global food system.

title: Maine Women: Living on the Land
description: Maine Women: Living on the Land celebrates the relationship between land and home. It is about what happens to the land we live on that creates the spirit and soul of a place. This documentary features ten Maine women who have lived most of their lives on the land either by producing a product or building a community. The stories these remarkable women share have a common thread in their sense of community and legacy of family traditions of work.

title: La gran aventura quinientos años después
Battle for the Klamath
description: Battle for the Klamath is a feature length documentary about the fight over water rights and salmon between environmentalists and Indian tribes on one side and small farmers and the Bush Adminstration on the other.

title: L'air et la mer au secours de la Terre
Back To The Disaster
description: A documentary on the band, Sugarcult filmed during the height of their success on their North American tour and in Japan as main support for Green Day. Sheds light on their interpersonal dynamics, letting you get to know each band member.

title: Manchester City FC: The Magic of the FA Cup
Des traces sous le bitume
description: Embarked in a convoy of old jalopies in a road movie between France and Mauritania, the directors meet unconventional characters living according to their own moral, and film their unorthodox portraits: a strange outing across the desert.

title: Jackson Skids
description: Shows the unique living situations that dedicated ski bums endure in order to live cheaply and pursue the dream of skiing everyday.

title: Decoding the Past: Prophecies of Iraq
Cinema
description: Experimental collage video art with Sindoval Aguiar.

title: Dustbreeders, Junko & Katie O'Looney live at Instants Chavirés 2004
description: Documenting Dustbreeders, Junko and Katie O'Looney live at Les Instants Chavirés (Montreuil, France) on June 10, 2004.

title: Batman Villains: Bob the Goon
description: Profile featurette on Tracey Walter's character in Batman (1989).

title: Return to the Border
description: In the past half-century, millions of people around the globe have sacrificed themselves for communism and socialism. In Return to the Border, a Chinese-born filmmaker reflects on the personal ramifications of these political ideals, from his memories of a childhood in the border town of Dandong to his experiences in North Korea. A PBS Indies / Global Voices selection.

title: Lost in Adaptation: Jonathan Coe
description: The film presents a wide ranging discussion about the fictional work of author Jonathan Coe that has been adapted for the screen.

title: The Sacramento: River of Life
description: A one hour journey examining the past and future of California's Sacramento River.

title: AK and Beyond
description: Inside the Production of 'First Descent'.

title: Hios: Myrovolos kai elkystiki olo to hrono
'do
description: Following a diverse group of five New Yorkers through five years and fourteen hairstyles, 'do uses the topic of how people feel about their hair as a means of exploring the relationship between appearance and identity. Through these personal stories, 'do explores issues of gender, race, sexual preference and socio-economic status, encouraging the audience to examine their own ideas about how we define ourselves - as feminine or masculine, banker or artist, gay or straight, black or white - through how we look.

title: Penguins Can Fly
description: In the summer of 2003, John Munro swam 36 hours from Sackets Harbor, New York to Kingston, Ontario to help his wife, marathon swimmer Vicki Keith, raise money for the Kingston Family YMCA's adaptive program for children with disabilities.

title: Love in La La Land?
description: In Los Angeles, a city full of beautiful people where temptation is very much alive, lies one burning question... Everyday people that inhabit and walk the streets of LA are asked... is there Love in La La Land?

title: The Gillian Film
description: Through an examination of one life defined a 'different" or "exceptional" The Gillian Film explores how we might transform our understanding of the meaning and worth of any individual life.

title: Kaiki! Unbelievable: Senritsu! Maisô sa reta Shashin
Kidnapped!
description: A couple mysteriously vanish after a romantic evening under the stars... A teenager disappears on her way home from school... A university graduate goes missing whilst holidaying in London... From the early 1970s to the mid-80s, scores of ordinary Japanese disappeared without a trace, many of them from beaches and remote villages along the Japan Sea coast, others from Tokyo, London and Madrid. After decades of speculation, it was finally revealed in 2002 that these ordinary Japanese citizens had in fact been abducted by North Korean spies as part of a bizarre and sinister plot of espionage by the hard-line, communist dictatorship of Kim Jong Il. From the last front of the Cold War to the new battle against the 'Axis of Evil', Kidnapped! tells the extraordinary story of the Chimura, Yokota and Arimoto families - some of the unfortunate victims of a terrifying abduction campaign by North Korea, and who are now unwittingly caught up in the eye of a political storm. The story of these families' dramatic 25-year struggle in search for the truth unveils a tangled web of bizarre abductions, political manoeuvrings and international espionage. Kidnapped! is an emotional and uncompromising journey into the most controversial issue in Japan today. It is a powerful account of the remarkable story of a group of ordinary Japanese citizens who are perhaps the last remaining casualties of the Cold War and who have become the latest pawns in a dubious, diplomatic chess game of life and death.

title: Intervention House
description: After struggling with drug addiction for 17 years and making it through recovery, Ricky and Melba McGee are determined to use their experiences to help other addicts get clean. In this debut episode, the residents of Intervention House are on an emotional edge when 30 year-old crack addict "Brenda" disappears; newly-arrived cocaine addict "Russ" reveals a secret about the depths to which his addicted girlfriend has fallen; and chronic alcoholic "Cheryl" moves in after drinking mouth wash and blacking-out. Melba also faces a personal crisis when she attempts to reunite with her gay son after more than a year of estrangement.

title: Escape from Iran: The Hollywood Option
description: 'Escape from Iran' commemorates the 25th anniversary of the 'Canadian Caper,' beginning with the direct testimony of the Americans who found sanctuary with the Canadian embassy in Tehran and the Canadians who risked their own safety to shelter their country's neighbors.

title: Surviving the Dungeon: The Legacy of Stu Hart
description: Deep in the Rocky Mountains - in the city of Calgary, Alberta Canada - lies the most famous training facility in the history of professional wrestling: the world-renowned Hart Dungeon. Since the 1950s, aspiring wrestlers from all over the world have come to the home of Stu Hart with the dream of learning the art of professional wrestling. In that time, Stu and his sons Bruce, Keith and Ross have helped shape the careers of some of the most celebrated figures in the sport, including champions such as Chris Jericho, Chris Benoit, "British Bulldog" Davey Boy Smith, Jim "The Anvil" Neidhart, Brian Pillman, Jushin "Thunder" Liger, Stu's sons Owen and Bret, and so many more. Now, for the very first time, experience the sacrifices Stu and his wife Helen had to make in order to survive in one of the most cutthroat businesses in the world, the talent that made their family into stars, and the courage that made them legends.

title: Histoire des automobiles Citroën: Un nom, une histoire, une technique
L'histoire naturelle d'Armand David
description: The life and work of French naturalist-scientist-priest Père Armand David, living as a missionary in China, who is thought to be the first Westerner ever to lay eyes on a wild panda as he was documenting species of Chinese flora and fauna.

title: Marriage Dialogues
description: A balanced, full-length documentary on the traditional versus same-sex marriage controversy.

title: Gold Mountain Ballad
description: Gold Mountain Ballad is a documentary about a Chinese Opera icon who gives up fame and fortune in her homeland to move to the United States for artistic freedom in pursuit of the American dream.

title: Pizza
description: A source of inspiration for the cinematography of Ugo Giorgetti, São Paulo is once again the backdrop to this documentary in which the theme is the specialty of the city's culinary.

title: The Eskimo and the Whale

This case of 'Baby Trading' reached the House of Commons where Prime Minister Tony Blair declared their actions 'deplorable'. The babies were taken into care and returned to the US social services. The Kilshaws and the mother, Tranda Wecker, who had 'sold her kids on the Internet', were vilified in the press and prevented from seeing the girls. But what was the real story? In 2005 this documentary revisits the story, discovering the main players still fighting for the right to bring up the now 5 year old girls. The Kilshaws are trying to highlight their case by standing in the General Election and the mother is battling with the Missouri Supreme Court trying to prove she was only seeking a good home for the girls, unable at the time to look after them herself, and certainly never received any money for them. The daughters meanwhile are unaware they are adopted. He has also become known for his ability to highlight the relationship between the artwork, the exhibition space, and the viewer. This documentary reveals the process of his major early work, "Under the Colors," which was first exhibited at MACA Gallery in Tokyo in 2004. The size of this painting is 380 x 1700cm (approx. 150 x 670 inches.) He spent 6 months to finish this piece. Instead of working on a single large canvas, he painted on smaller canvases and then combined them into one in the exhibition space. Since he worked in a small studio, he had no chance to view the entire piece until he installed. During the process, he patiently kept putting paint on the canvas repeatedly. The filmmaker visited his studio to document the art-making process every two weeks. This film shows the art-making process without narration, voice-over and interview.

description: In America if you want to get adopted, you've got to get yourself noticed. Justine and Lakeisha are two 14 year olds who are doing just that. They take part in uniquely American marketing techniques, including adoption parties and TV shows, to attract interest in them while they search for families to give them a lifetime commitment - something they didn't get from their parents. Justine lives in a small town in Massachusetts. A bubbly personality, she was taken into care when she was eleven. She'd lived in various 'bridge homes' until her best friend persuaded her parents to foster her. Although Justine appears to have settled in, she feels like an outsider. "I feel weird going into the fridge, it's not really my house, what am I doing going into their fridge, eating their food". Lakeisha has moved from one foster home to another in and around Boston since she was a baby. Her unruly behaviour has made adoption difficult - until the Jones' spot her at an adoption party. They are a successful black family with high expectations of Lakeisha. "They have their own rules set up for me and I have my rules set up for them - doesn't mean we're each gonna follow them, of course everybody breaks the rules. That's life." This film follows the girls' search for unconditional love within a family, but this doesn't come as easily as they think.

title: The Lamentations Series: The Ninth Night and Day
description: While the ten-day ceremony 'Âshûrâ' is a commemoration of the slaughter of the grandson of the prophet Muhammad and his relatives and companions at Karbalâ' in 680, it is also an invocation of the occulted Twelfth Imam, the Mahdî, in the hope of hurrying his exoteric earthly return. But how would the one invoked, who is (imaginally) present albeit occulted, perceive the ceremony? He would not perceive it the way we see it but in more temporal detail. While the first part of the video appears to be a documentation of the ceremony as it might be perceived by an all too human audience member, the second part of the video, which happens across a lapse of consciousness if not of being (indicated by the cut to black on the sound of the participants' hands striking their chests), and where time is dilated, implies that the essential spectator of the ceremony is the one to whom it is addressed, the Mahdî. While the participants' self-flagellation is excessive, it is even more so when perceived by its essential addressee, the Mahdî, who has keen (hadîd) perception. The video's subtitle subtly implies another excess since its "night and day" refers not only to (something that continues for) one day and one night, the ninth, but also to something that goes on all the time ("night and day: all the time" ["Oxford Dictionary of English," 3rd edition, 2016]).

En 2002, la politique visant à lutter contre la délinquance juvénile, fer de lance de la campagne présidentielle, annonçait l'ouverture des premiers Centres Educatifs Fermés. Le CEF de la plaine du Forez (Loire) a vu le jour en 2004. Dix mineurs délinquants de 13 à 16 ans au lourd parcours pénal y sont placés. « Educatif » « Fermé ». Toute l'ambiguïté du CEF repose sur cette dualité.

Ce documentaire prend le temps de plonger dans le quotidien du centre et de son projet éducatif, pour raconter l'histoire de ceux qui le vivent. -Point de chute- aborde la problématique de la délinquance juvénile sous l'angle du dialogue, de la reconstruction, et du regard vers demain.

title: A Ballad for My Son
description: August 2005, Israel is about to withdraw from Gaza. This year is also a turning point for Daniel and Elad. Both are joining the army. They are only 18, yet they are convinced that they chose the right way. Daniel is willing to sacrifice his freedom and Elad his life. Will they succeed to achieve their goals? And who will be accountable if they fail? The film deals with choices that never before confronted the young Israelis. This is a story of a divided country and its children who are searching for a way, of big dreams and small dreams, of people and land, and parents who are afraid for their sons.

title: Totems to Turquois
description: For thousands of years the native peoples of North America have made extraordinary jewelry, which is the focus of this cinematic documentary shot in the Summer of 2004 on location in Arizona, New Mexico, Alaska, and British Columbia. This photographic and combined multi media exhibit initially premiered at the American Museum of Natural History (October 30, 2004 - July 10, 2005) and then exhibited around the world until 2015.

title: En gal en elsker eller en poet
description: This film describes H.C.Andersen and his primary tool, - language. H.C. Andersen was a traveler. He set out on his many travels, returning home with an enriched Danish language. Through discussion, Kathrine Lilleør, Johannes Møllehave and Niels Birger Wamberg unveil the works of Andersen's vibrant language.

title: L' Arbre et le feu
description: In Madagascar, fire is considered a blessing. In modern societies, fire can be an ecological disaster. But for the Tanala mountain indigenous tribe, fire represents more than just an ancestral method of acquiring land for rice cultivation. To them, it signifies a connection with the gods. Today, Madagascar is also known as the Red Island due to its distinctive red soil, which becomes increasingly prominent across large areas of the territory due to deforestation. This documentary explores the contrasting perspectives of the high-altitude Malagasy people and the American scientists who seek to 'save the world'.
